commit.message:
Add Emacs backup pattern

Emacs uses *~ as backup files.  Ignore them.

Signed-off-by: Yasushi SHOJI <yashi@spacecubics.com>

Search executable in exec-path unless absolute path

Search executable file in `exec-path` using `executable-find` if the
executable in the record is not absolute path.  This makes julia-repl
align with other Emacs packages using `call-process` or
`start-process`.

Signed-off-by: Yasushi SHOJI <yashi@spacecubics.com>

commit.message:
Replace positional args with keyword args in define-minor-mode

Positional arguments in `define-minor-mode` have been deprecated since emacs version 21 and were producing a warning
message in message in emacs 27. This changeset replaces positional arguments with keyword arguments.

Extend EmacsVterm.jl interface to be future-proof

The idea is that the code in EmacsVterm.jl can specify which kind of
data it is sending to Emacs and Emacs will decide how to display the
data.

Currently, the only supported kind of data is "documentation", which
is shown in the *julia-doc* buffer, but later, things like inline
display of images or rendered latex code might be added. If the user
has a newer version of EmacsVterm.jl trying to send data not supported
by user's version of julia-repl, an error message is shown.
Don't use deprecated symbol t in pcase

Use shr to render HTML documentation and view with view-mode

The code is simpler than with eww and allows the user to configure
how the documentation is shown with `display-buffer-alist`.
